Le Étudiants de Velours in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivals that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velour Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of upper and secondary schools.
The festival's cloud consists of two concerts organized on 17 November.
Charles University has an important part in this festival.
"Among the choirs there is the Choeur of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," said the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The festival's clou is the concert of the Choeur des lycées and secondary classes that takes place with free entrance on 17 November from 14 hours on the space in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
In the program there is the composition of well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velours" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the upper schools as well as that of Charles University occur.
The aim of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to recall the 22nd anniversary of the Velor Revolution, but also to present to the public a chorus music of the highest level and develop creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Hearts in cooperation with the lycée Jan Kepler.
All the action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival is held from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, student encounters and other activities.
Interested will find all information on the Internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
