How to detect a lie
A look at recent headlines indicates the extent to which deception and lies are omnipresent in everyday life.
The Republican candidate to the presidency, Herman Cain, is busy exchanging sexual harassment allegations with several women, each on the other accusing the other of lying.
The Penn State administrators were accused of betting for allegedly covering reports that a retired football coach had sexually assaulted boys.
